            "__cdata": "<p class=\"p_20\">31. A 90-year-old man presents to accident and emergency with a 2-week history of fevers, lethargy and night sweats. He has recently had crowns fitted at the dentists.He has a past medical history of hypertension, gout and type 2 diabetes mellitus. On examination his temperature is 39°C, his pulse is 120 bpm and splinter haemorrhages are seen in the nails. On auscultation of the heart a pan systolic murmur is audible. A diagnosis of endocarditis is suspected and blood cultures are taken. What organism is most likely to be grown?</p>"
